        },
        "body": "### ✨ Overview\r\nThis PR introduces a new file, `contribution_guide.md`, aimed at helping beginners navigate open source contributions during Hacktoberfest 2025.  \r\nIt provides a step-by-step guide for getting started, making meaningful contributions, and submitting pull requests.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### 📘 Contents of the Guide\r\n- How to find projects suitable for Hacktoberfest participation  \r\n- Instructions to fork a repository, clone it locally, and create branches  \r\n- Guidelines for making changes, committing, and pushing code  \r\n- How to open a Pull Request and get it reviewed  \r\n- Best practices and tips for respectful, effective contributions  \r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### 🎯 Purpose\r\nThe goal of this guide is to simplify the onboarding process for new contributors, encourage active participation, and ensure they follow good practices while contributing to open source projects.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### 💬 Feedback\r\nContributors and maintainers are welcome to suggest improvements, additional tips, or clarifications to make this guide more beginner-friendly.\r\n",
